  "response_text": "It opens on a painted, carnival-style cutout board inside a bright, simple setting. The illustration shows a cheerful cartoon figure with oversized ears, a dark hat, a striped tie, and large gloved hands holding a hamburger on one side and a napkin or wrapper on the other. A real person’s face appears through a round hole where the cartoon face would be. First, a smiling woman with short dark hair looks forward from inside the cutout. The painted hamburger is large and close to the foreground, with a rounded bun and dark topping visible.\n\nThe same playful cutout remains, but different faces appear in the opening. A younger woman with long light-brown hair leans in and looks directly ahead. Then an older man wearing a broad tan cowboy hat fills the face opening, his expression more serious. After him, a Black man appears in the same place, smiling broadly. The repeated image makes it look as if a variety of customers are taking turns becoming the cartoon hamburger eater.\n\nThe scene changes to a close display of fresh hamburger toppings arranged on a tabletop. At first, the view is crowded with a red tomato beaded with moisture, a whole pale onion, a head of green lettuce with crinkled leaves, and a shallow bowl of glossy yellow condiment swirled on the surface. Nearby are pieces of tomato and other produce, all lit warmly so the colors look rich and appetizing.\n\nThe display gradually reveals more ingredients. The lettuce remains central while a block of yellow cheese and slices of cheese appear to the right. Pale onion rounds sit in front, and brown whole onions with papery skins come into view. Behind them are glass jars and more toppings. The arrangement looks like a still life of hamburger fixings: lettuce, tomatoes, onions, cheese, and sauces packed closely together.\n\nAs the view continues across the tabletop, an open glass jar filled with thick red ketchup becomes prominent. Around it are whole brown onions and glossy green pickles, including cut pickle pieces in the foreground. The cheese block stays behind the jar, and leafy lettuce remains in the background. The ingredients are displayed as abundant and varied, spread across the surface rather than hidden in packaging.\n\nA finished hamburger then comes into view on the right side of the ingredient display. It has a smooth, rounded top bun, a thick red tomato slice, ruffled green lettuce, a square beef patty, melted yellow cheese, and a bottom bun. The burger sits among the same toppings: the open ketchup jar to its left, pickles in front, and fresh tomatoes behind and beside it. As the burger becomes centered, sliced tomatoes and whole tomatoes fill the right side of the scene, reinforcing the idea of a heavily topped hamburger.\n\nThe final image shows the exterior of a Wendy’s restaurant from across a street. The low, rectangular building has a red Wendy’s sign on the front and a large yellow sign reading “HAMBURGERS,” with additional smaller wording suggesting “old fashioned” hamburgers. A tall roadside sign with the Wendy’s branding stands near the building. Cars are parked around the restaurant, trees rise behind it, and the setting looks like a suburban roadside fast-food location in daylight.",
